When a cell selected into the preliminary E-DCH active set is not included into the final E-DCH active set because the cell does not satisfy E-DCH active set acceptance condition "CPICHEcNoNonEDCHNCell < CPICHEcNoEDCHServingCell + EDCHAddEcNoOffset".

kpi_info.title: DL_DCH_SEL_HSDPA_POWER_INT
kpi_info.use: The number of times when HS-DSCH downlink transport channel cannot be selected for an interactive class connection due to downlink power limits.When HS-DSCH cannot be selected as downlink transport channel due to condition PtxTotal>PtxTargetHSDPA or PtxNC>PtxTargetHSDPA.

kpi_info.title: DL_DCH_SEL_HSDPA_POWER_BGR
kpi_info.use: The number of times when HS-DSCH downlink transport channel cannot be selected for a background class connection due to downlink power limits. When HS-DSCH cannot be selected as downlink transport channel due to condition PtxTotal>PtxTargetHSDPA or PtxNC>PtxTargetHSDPA.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_UE_INT
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to UE for interactive class connections. When the RNC has received an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message from the UE during the E-DCH setup or a timer waiting for the RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE expires.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_UE_BGR
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to UE for background class connections. When the RNC has received an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message from the UE during the E-DCH setup or a timer waiting for the RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE expires.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_BTS_INT
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to BTS for interactive class connections. When the RNC receives an NBAP: RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION FAILURE or NBAP: RADIO LINK SETUP FAILURE message during the E-DCH setup or a timer waiting for the acknowledgement message expires.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_BTS_BGR
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to BTS for background class connections. When the RNC receives an NBAP: RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION FAILURE or NBAP: RADIO LINK SETUP FAILURE message during the E-DCH setup or a timer waiting for the acknowledgement message expires.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_TRANS_INT
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to transport for interactive class connections. When the E-DCH setup fails due to Iub transport resource allocation failure.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_TRANS_BGR
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to transport for background class connections. When the E-DCH setup fails due to Iub transport resource allocation failure.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_OTHER_INT
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures for interactive class connections due to reasons not covered by the other failure counters, for example due to RNC internal failures. When the E-DCH setup fails due to some reason not covered by the other failure counters.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_OTHER_BGR
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures for background class connections due to reasons not covered by the other failure counters, for example due to RNC internal failures. When the E-DCH setup fails due to some reason not covered by the other failure counters.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_SUCCESS_EDCH_INT
kpi_info.use: The number of successful E-DCH allocations for interactive class connections. When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE after a successful E-DCH setup or upgrade from DCH. The counter is updated also when the RNC receives RRC: ACTIVE SET UPDATE COMPLETE after a successful addition of a cell into the E-DCH active set.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_SUCCESS_EDCH_BGR
kpi_info.use: The number of successful E-DCH allocations for interactive class connections. When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE after a successful E-DCH setup or upgrade from DCH. The counter is updated also when the RNC receives RRC: ACTIVE SET UPDATE COMPLETE after a successful addition of a cell into the E-DCH active set.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_EDCH_INT
kpi_info.use: The sum of E-DCH allocation durations for interactive class connections. This counter is updated with a 1-second sampling interval during the E-DCH allocation time. The remaining time is updated to the counter when the E-DCH is released.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_EDCH_BGR
kpi_info.use: The sum of E-DCH allocation durations for background class connections. This counter is updated with a 1-second sampling interval during the E-DCH allocation time. The remaining time is updated to the counter when the E-DCH is released.

kpi_info.title: REL_EDCH_NORM_INT
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH normal releases in the SRNC for interactive class connections. When the E-DCH is released with normal cause, i.e. not due to any failure situation.

kpi_info.title: REL_EDCH_NORM_BGR
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH normal releases in the SRNC for background class connections. When the E-DCH is released with normal cause, i.e. not due to any failure situation.

kpi_info.title: REL_EDCH_HSDSCH_SCC_INT
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH releases due to HS-DSCH serving cell change for interactive class connections, i.e. the new HS-DSCH serving cell does not support E-DCH. When the E-DCH is released due to HS-DSCH serving cell.

kpi_info.title: REL_EDCH_HSDSCH_SCC_BGR
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH releases due to HS-DSCH serving cell change for background class connections, i.e. the new HS-DSCH serving cell does not support E-DCH. When the E-DCH is released due to HS-DSCH serving cell.

kpi_info.title: REL_EDCH_RL_FAIL_INT
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH releases for interactive class connections due to radio link failure, uplink RLC unrecoverable error or UE not responding to an RRC message sent by the RNC. When the E-DCH is released due to radio link failure, uplink RLC unrecoverable error or UE not responding to an RRC message.

kpi_info.title: REL_EDCH_RL_FAIL_BGR
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH releases for background class connections due to radio link failure, uplink RLC unrecoverable error or UE not responding to an RRC message sent by the RNC. When the E-DCH is released due to radio link failure, uplink RLC unrecoverable error or UE not responding to an RRC message.

kpi_info.title: REL_EDCH_OTHER_FAIL_INT
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH releases due to other failure reason for interactive class connections. When the E-DCH is released due to other failure reason than radio link failure or uplink RLC unrecoverable error.

kpi_info.title: REL_EDCH_OTHER_FAIL_BGR
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH releases due to other failure reason for background class connections. When the E-DCH is released due to other failure reason than radio link failure or uplink RLC unrecoverable error.

kpi_info.title: AMR_EDCH_ALLO
kpi_info.use: The number of AMR + E-DCH multi-RAB allocations. When AMR DCH or PS NRT E-DCH setup is successful, and the result is AMR + E-DCH multi RAB.

kpi_info.title: AMR_EDCH_NORMAL_REL
kpi_info.use: The number of AMR + E-DCH multi-RAB normal releases. When AMR + E-DCH multi RAB exists and either of the connections is released with normal cause.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_HS_INTER_RNC_HHO_INT
kpi_info.use: The number of successful HS-DSCH allocations for incoming Inter-RNC HHO for interactive class connections. Also counter M1002C385 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED:When the target-RNC of Inter-RNC HHO has successfully allocated resources for an HS-DSCH user plane and sends RANAP: RELOCATION REQUEST ACKNOWLEDGE to the core network.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_HS_INTER_RNC_HHO_BGR
kpi_info.use: The number of successful HS-DSCH allocations for incoming Inter-RNC HHO for background class connections. Also counter M1002C389 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED:When the target-RNC of Inter-RNC HHO has successfully allocated resources for an HS-DSCH user plane and sends RANAP: RELOCATION REQUEST ACKNOWLEDGE to the core network.

kpi_info.title: STP_F_HS_INTER_RNC_HHO_INT
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH setup failures for incoming Inter-RNC HHO for interactive class connections. Also one of the basic HS-DSCH setup failure counters is updated along with this counter. UPDATED:When the resource allocation for HS-DSCH user plane fails in the target-RNC of an inter-RNC HHO.

kpi_info.title: STP_F_HS_INTER_RNC_HHO_BGR
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH setup failures for incoming Inter-RNC HHO for background class connections. Also one of the basic HS-DSCH setup failure counters is updated along with this counter. UPDATED:When the resource allocation for HS-DSCH user plane fails in the target-RNC of an inter-RNC HHO.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_ED_INTER_RNC_HHO_INT
kpi_info.use: The number of successful E-DCH allocations for incoming Inter-RNC HHO for interactive class connections. M1002C531 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED:When the target-RNC of Inter-RNC HHO has successfully allocated resources for an HS-DSCH/E-DCH user plane and sends RANAP: RELOCATION REQUEST ACKNOWLEDGE to the core network.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_ED_INTER_RNC_HHO_BGR
kpi_info.use: The number of successful E-DCH allocations for incoming Inter-RNC HHO for background class connections. M1002C532 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED:When the target-RNC of Inter-RNC HHO has successfully allocated resources for an HS-DSCH/E-DCH user plane and sends RANAP: RELOCATION REQUEST ACKNOWLEDGE to the core network.

kpi_info.title: STP_F_ED_INTER_RNC_HHO_INT
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures for incoming Inter-RNC HHO for interactive class connections. Also one of the basic E-DCH setup failure counters is updated along with this counter. UPDATED:When the resource allocation for HS-DSCH/E-DCH user plane fails in the target-RNC of an inter-RNC HHO.

kpi_info.title: STP_F_ED_INTER_RNC_HHO_BGR
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures for incoming Inter-RNC HHO for background class connections. Also one of the basic E-DCH setup failure counters is updated along with this counter. UPDATED:When the resource allocation for HS-DSCH/E-DCH user plane fails in the target-RNC of an inter-RNC HHO.

kpi_info.title: REJ_DCH_DUE_CODES_INT_DL
kpi_info.use: The number of NRT DCH setup rejects for interactive traffic class due to running out of channelization codes in DL. UPDATED: When admission control rejects interactive DCH setup due to running out of channelization codes in DL. This counter includes initial DCH setups, handover attempts and channel type switches from HS-DSCH to DCH.

kpi_info.title: REJ_DCH_DUE_CODES_BGR_DL
kpi_info.use: The number of NRT DCH setup rejects for background traffic class due to running out of codes in DL. UPDATED: When admission control rejects background DCH setup due to running out of channelization codes in DL. This counter includes initial DCH setups, handover attempts and channel type switches from HS-DSCH to DCH.

kpi_info.title: REJ_DCH_DUE_POWER_INT_DL
kpi_info.use: The number of NRT DCH setup rejects for interactive traffic class due to power limits in DL. UPDATED: When admission control rejects interactive DCH setup due to power limits in DL. This counter includes initial DCH setups, handover attempts and channel type switches from HS-DSCH to DCH.

kpi_info.title: REJ_DCH_DUE_POWER_BGR_DL
kpi_info.use: The number of NRT DCH setup rejects for background traffic class due to power limits in DL. UPDATED: When admission control rejects background DCH setup due to power limits in DL. This counter includes initial DCH setups, handover attempts and channel type switches from HS-DSCH to DCH.

kpi_info.title: REJ_DCH_REC_DUE_CODES_INT_DL
kpi_info.use: The number of NRT DCH reconfiguration rejects for interactive traffic class due to running out of channelization codes in DL. UPDATED: When admission control rejects interactive DCH reconfiguration due to running out of channelization codes in DL.

kpi_info.title: REJ_DCH_REC_DUE_CODES_BGR_DL
kpi_info.use: The number of NRT DCH reconfiguration rejects for background traffic class due to running out of channelization codes in DL. UPDATED: When admission control rejects background DCH reconfiguration due to running out of channelization codes in DL.

kpi_info.title: REJ_DCH_REC_DUE_PWR_INT_DL
kpi_info.use: The number of NRT DCH reconfiguration rejects for interactive traffic class due to power limits in DL. UPDATED: When admission control rejects interactive DCH reconfiguration due to power limits in DL.

kpi_info.title: REJ_DCH_REC_DUE_PWR_BGR_DL
kpi_info.use: The number of NRT DCH reconfiguration rejects for background traffic class due to power limits in DL. UPDATED: When admission control rejects background DCH reconfiguration due to power limits in DL.

kpi_info.title: AMR_LOWER_CODEC_SF128_INC
kpi_info.use: The number of times when AMR codec mode set {5.9, 4.75} on SF128 is selected for an incoming call. This does not mean that SF128 would really be taken into use but is just a proposal from the load control entity of a single cell in UEs active set. UPDATED: When admission control selects SF128 code for an incoming AMR call with codec {5.9, 4.75}.

kpi_info.title: AMR_LOWER_CODEC_SF256_INC
kpi_info.use: The number of times when AMR codec mode set {5.9, 4.75} on SF256 is selected for an incoming call. This does not mean that SF256 would really be taken into use but is just a proposal from the load control entity of a single cell in UEs active set. UPDATED: When admission control selects SF256 code for an incoming AMR call with codec {5.9, 4.75}.

kpi_info.title: LOAD_AMR_DGR_SF128_SUCCESS
kpi_info.use: The number of successful load triggered AMR codec mode downgrades to set {5.9, 4.75} on SF128. This counter is updated only for the cell that triggered the codec downgrade. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE from the UE indicating a successful AMR codec downgrade.

kpi_info.title: LOAD_AMR_DGR_SF256_SUCCESS
kpi_info.use: The number of successful load triggered AMR codec mode downgrades to set {5.9, 4.75} on SF256. This counter is updated only for the cell that triggered the codec downgrade. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE from the UE indicating a successful AMR codec downgrade.

kpi_info.title: LOAD_AMR_UPGRADE_SUCCESS
kpi_info.use: The number of AMR codec upgrades due to load thresholds. This counter is updated only for the cell that triggered the upgrade procedure. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE from the UE indicating a successful AMR codec upgrade.

kpi_info.title: AMR_CODEC_CHANGE_FAIL_ICSU
kpi_info.use: The number of AMR codec changes prevented by the ICSU unit load. UPDATED: When ICSU load threshold prevents changing the AMR codec.

kpi_info.title: AMR_CODEC_CHANGE_FAIL_OTHER
kpi_info.use: The number of AMR codec changes that failed due to other reason than one of the following: ICSU load, other active set cells do not have the needed AMR mode set enabled, other active set cells are not in underload state, the active set has changed during the last five seconds or another parallel procedure is ongoing for the same UE. UPDATED: When AMR codec mode change fails for example due to UE replying with RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE.

kpi_info.title: SWI_DCH_TO_HS_DSCH_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of successful channel switches made directly from the DCH xx/yy to the HS-DSCH for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the user's DCH user plane allocation is switched to the HS-DSCH without first downgrading to the DCH 0/0.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_HS_DSCH_FLOW_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH MAC-d flow allocations in the SRNC for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the RNC has received an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE - after successful HS-DSCH MAC-d flow setup.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_HS_DSCH_RET_16_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of allocations for 16 kbps HS-DSCH return channels (DCH UL) for the streaming traffic. UPDATED: When the RNC receives an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE after a successful HS-DSCH return channel setup or bit rate modification.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_HS_DSCH_RET_64_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH 64 kbps return channel (DCH UL) allocations in the SRNC for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the RNC has received an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE - after successful HS-DSCH return channel setup or bit rate modification.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_HS_DSCH_RET_128_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH 128 kbps return channel (DCH UL) allocations in the SRNC for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the RNC has received an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE - after successful HS-DSCH return channel setup or bit rate modification.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_HS_DSCH_FLOW_STR
kpi_info.use: The sum of HS-DSCH MAC-d flow allocation durations in the SRNC for streaming class connections. UPDATED: This counter is updated with a one-second sampling interval during the MAC-d flow allocation time.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_HS_DSCH_RET_16_STR
kpi_info.use: The sum of DCH allocation durations for 16 kbps HS-DSCH return channels for the streaming traffic. UPDATED: The counter is updated at one-second sampling intervals during the DCH allocation time.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_HS_DSCH_RET_64_STR
kpi_info.use: The sum of 64 kbps return channel allocation durations in the SRNC for streaming class connections. UPDATED: This counter is updated with a one-second sampling interval during the DCH allocation time.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_HS_DSCH_RET_128_STR
kpi_info.use: The sum of 128 kbps return channel allocation durations in the SRNC for streaming class connections. UPDATED: This counter is updated with a one-second sampling interval during the DCH allocation time.

kpi_info.title: REJ_HS_DSCH_RET_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of failed allocations for the HS-DSCH transport channel due to lack of radio resources for the UL DCH return channel for streaming class connections. After rejection the capacity request is sent back to the PS queue and the HS-DSCH channel type UPDATED: When UL DCH for HS-DSCH return channel cannot be allocated.

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_NORM_HS_DSCH_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH MAC-d flow normal releases in the SRNC for streaming class connections. Includes also HS-DSCH releases due to 1A event triggered state transitions to FACH. UPDATED: When the HS-DSCH MAC-d flow and its return channel allocations are released with normal cause.

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_OTH_FAIL_HSDSCH_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH allocation releases due to other than radio link failure in the SRNC for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the HS-DSCH MAC-d flow and its return channel allocations are released with a failure cause other than radio link failure.

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_HS_DSCH_MOB_DCH_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH releases due to mobility-related HS-DSCH to DCH transitions in the SRNC for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the HS-DSCH MAC-d flow and its return channel allocations are released due to mobility-related HS-DSCH to DCH transition. The reasons for release can be for example IFHO/ISHO measurements for AMR multi-service, low UL SIRerror value, removal of HS-DSCH radio link due to event 1B/1C, radio link failure, Rx-Tx time difference measurement, relocation of HS-DSCH radio link or event 6A.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_RNC_HS_DSCH_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH setup failures due to RNC internal reasons (including RNC internal transport) in the SRNC for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the HS-DSCH MAC-d flow or return channel setup fails due to RNC internal reasons.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_IUB_MAC_D_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH MAC-d flow setup failures due to Iub transport in the SRNC for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the setup of Iub transport resources fails for MAC-d flow. The counter is also updated if HS-DSCH cannot be allocated due to NbrOfOverbookedHSDPAUsers limitation.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_UE_HS_DSCH_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH setup failures due to UE in the SRNC for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the RNC has received an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message from the UE or NBAP: RADIO LINK FAILURE INDICATION from the BTS during the HS-DSCH setup, or a timer waiting for the RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message expires.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_BTS_HS_DSCH_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH setup failures due to BTS in the SRNC for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the RNC receives an NBAP: RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION FAILURE or NBAP: RADIO LINK SETUP FAILURE message during the transition to HS-DSCH or a timer waiting for the acknowledgement message to expire.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_IUB_HS_TOTAL_STR
kpi_info.use: The total number of HS-DSCH setup failures due Iub transport in the SRNC for streaming class connections. This counter is equal to the sum of M1002C586, M1002C587, M1002C588 and M1002C582. UPDATED: When the setup of Iub transport resources fails for either the MAC-d flow or the return channel.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_16_IUB_HSDSCH_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH setup failures due to the 16 kbps return channel Iub transport for streaming traffic class connections. UPDATED: The counter is updated by one when the setup of Iub transport resources fails for the 16 kbps return channel.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_64_IUB_HSDSCH_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH setup failures due to the 64 kbps return channel Iub transport in the SRNC for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the setup of Iub transport resources fails for the 64 kbps return channel.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_128_IUB_HSDSCH_ST
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH failures due to the 128 kbps return channel Iub transport in the SRNC for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the setup of Iub transport resources fails for the 128 kbps return channel.

kpi_info.title: HS_DSCH_RET_UPGRADE_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of DCH allocations with streaming class due to HSDPA return channel (DCH UL) upgrade. NOTE: Currently this counter is never updated because return channel upgrades are never performed on Streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the RNC has received an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE - after successful HS-DSCH return channel upgrade.

kpi_info.title: HS_DSCH_RET_DOWNGRADE_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of DCH allocations with streaming class due to HSDPA return channel (DCH UL) downgrade. NOTE: Currently this counter is never updated because return channel downgrades are never performed on Streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the RNC has received an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE - after successful HS-DSCH return channel downgrade.

kpi_info.title: DCH_SEL_MAX_HSDPA_USERS_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of times when the DCH channel type is selected for streaming class connections due to maximum amount of HSDPA users or MAC-d flows in the WBTS, local cell group or cell. UPDATED: During the NRT channel type selection if the DCH channel type is selected due to maximum amount of HSDPA users or MAC-d flows in the WBTS, local cell group or cell.

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_HS_DSCH_OTH_DCH_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH allocation normal releases due to other than mobility-related HS-DSCH to DCH switch (e.g. multi-RAB restrictions) for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the user's HS-DSCH allocation is released due to other than mobility-related HS-DSCH to DCH switch.

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_HS_DSCH_PRE_EMP_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH allocation normal releases due to pre-emptions for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the user's HS-DSCH allocation is released due to pre-emption.

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_RL_FAIL_HS_DSCH_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH allocation releases due to radio link failure, RLC protocol reset or uplink RLC unrecoverable error for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the user's HS-DSCH allocation is released due to radio link failure, RLC protocol reset or uplink RLC unrecoverable error (Cell Update sent by UE).

kpi_info.title: REJ_HS_DSCH_AMR_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of times that admission control rejects setting up an AMR + HS-DSCH connection for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When allocating AMR + HS-DSCH multi RAB is not possible because of admission control rejection.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_HS_DSCH_AMR_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of setup failures for AMR + HS-DSCH for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When DCH or HS-DSCH setup fails and the result would have been AMR + HS-DSCH multi RAB.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_HS_DSCH_AMR_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of AMR + HS-DSCH multi-RAB allocations for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When DCH or HS-DSCH mac-d flow setup is successful, and the result is AMR + HS-DSCH multi RAB.

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_NORM_HSDSCH_AMR_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of AMR + HS-DSCH multi-RAB normal releases for streaming class connections (one of the RBs is released). UPDATED: When AMR + HS-DSCH multi RAB exists and either of the connections is released with normal cause.

kpi_info.title: UL_DCH_SEL_MAX_HSUPA_USR_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of times when the E-DCH uplink transport channel cannot be selected for a streaming class connection in this cell due to maximum amount of E-DCH users in the cell or in the local cell group. UPDATED: When the E-DCH cannot be selected as the uplink transport channel in this cell because the number of E-DCH users in the cell would exceed the limit defined by MaxNumberEDCHCell or the number of E-DCH users in local cell group would exceed MaxNumberEDCHLCG

kpi_info.title: UL_DCH_SEL_BTS_HW_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of times when the E-DCH uplink transport channel cannot be selected for a streaming class connection in this cell because the BTS has reported that it has no capacity available for the E-DCH. UPDATED: When the E-DCH cannot be selected as the uplink transport channel in this cell because the BTS has reported with a RADIO RESOURCE MEASUREMENT REPORT message to be in a state where there is no capacity available for the E-DCH.

kpi_info.title: EDCH_ALLO_CANC_NA_AS_STR
kpi_info.use: The number of times when the E-DCH allocation made by the cell specific packet scheduler for a streaming class connection is cancelled due to a non-acceptable E-DCH active set. UPDATED: When a cell selected into the preliminary E-DCH active set is not included in the final E-DCH active set because the cell does not satisfy the E-DCH active set acceptance condition "CPICHEcNoNonEDCHNCell < CPICHEcNoEDCHServingCell + EDCHAddEcNoOffset".

kpi_info.title: DL_DCH_SEL_HSDPA_POWER_STR

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_UE_STR

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_BTS_STR

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_TRANS_STR

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_OTHER_STR

kpi_info.title: ALLO_SUCCESS_EDCH_STR

UPDATED: When the RNC receives an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE after a successful E-DCH setup or upgrade from the DCH. kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_EDCH_STR
kpi_info.use: The sum of E-DCH allocation durations for streaming class connections. UPDATED: This counter is updated with one-second sampling intervals during the E-DCH allocation time.

kpi_info.title: REL_EDCH_NORM_STR

kpi_info.title: REL_EDCH_HSDSCH_SCC_STR

kpi_info.title: REL_EDCH_RL_FAIL_STR

kpi_info.title: REL_EDCH_OTHER_FAIL_STR

kpi_info.title: ALLO_ED_INTER_RNC_HHO_STR

kpi_info.title: ALLO_AMR_RT_NRT_HSPA

kpi_info.title: ALLO_AMR_RT_MULTINRT_HSPA

kpi_info.title: ALLO_RT_NRT_HSPA
kpi_info.use: The number of allocations for RT_HSPA + NRT_HSPA. UPDATED: When HSPA bearer is successfully established forming combination RT_HSPA + NRT_HSPA.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_RT_MULTINRT_HSPA
kpi_info.use: The number of allocations for RT_HSPA + more than one NRT_HSPA. UPDATED:When HSPA bearer is successfully established forming combination RT_HSPA + n*NRT_HSPA.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_CM_HSDPA_IFHO

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DURA_CM_HSDPA_IFHO

kpi_info.title: REJ_CM_HSDPA_IFHO

kpi_info.title: REJ_DCH_DUE_POWER_INT_UL

kpi_info.title: REJ_DCH_DUE_POWER_BGR_UL

kpi_info.title: REJ_DCH_REC_DUE_PWR_INT_UL

kpi_info.use: The number of NRT DCH reconfiguration rejects for background traffic class due to power limits in UL. UPDATED: When admission control rejects background DCH reconfiguration due to power limits in UL.

kpi_info.title: ATT_HS_DSCH_DRNC

kpi_info.title: ATT_EDCH_DRNC

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_EDCH_DRNC

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_TRANS_HS_DSCH_AMR

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_TRANS_EDCH_AMR

Note that in case of IP-based Iub this includes also the cases when the BTS returns NBAP failure cause "Transport resources Unavailable" in NBAP: RADIO LINK SETUP FAILURE or NBAP: RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION FAILURE.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_OTHER_EDCH_AMR
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures for CS Voice call due to reasons not covered by the other failure counters, for example due to RNC internal failures. UPDATED:When the CS Voice E-DCH setup fails due to some other reason that is not covered by the other failure counters.

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_NORM_HS_DSCH_AMR

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_OTH_FAIL_HSDSCH_AMR

kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH normal releases in the SRNC for CS Voice call. UPDATED:When the E-DCH allocation is released with normal cause.

kpi_info.use: The number of successful HSPA channel type switches from HS-DSCH/E-DCH to Rel99 for CS Voice call. UPDATED:When a UE acknowledges a successful channel type switch from HS-DCSH/E-DCH to Rel99.

kpi_info.use: The number of successful allocations for 5.9 kbps HS-DSCH in SRNC for CS Voice call. UPDATED:When a UE acknowledges that HS-DSCH is successfully established. This can happen either in initial allocation (RAB setup), serving cell change or channel type switch.

kpi_info.use: The number of successful allocations for 12.65 kbps HS-DSCH in SRNC for CS Voice call. UPDATED:When a UE acknowledges that HS-DSCH is successfully established. This can happen either in initial allocation (RAB setup), serving cell change or channel type switch.

kpi_info.use: The sum of allocation durations for 5.9 kbps HS-DSCH in the SRNC for CS Voice call. UPDATED:This counter is updated with a 1 second interval during the HS-DSCH allocation time.

kpi_info.use: The sum of allocation durations for 12.2 kbps HS-DSCH in the SRNC for CS Voice call. UPDATED:This counter is updated with a 1 second interval during the HS-DSCH allocation time.

kpi_info.use: The sum of allocation durations for 12.65 kbps E-DCH in the SRNC for CS Voice call. UPDATED:This counter is updated with a 1 second interval during the E-DCH allocation time.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_HS_DSCH_SRB_SRNC

kpi_info.title: ALLO_HS_DSCH_SRB_DRNC
kpi_info.use: The number of successful HS-DSCH resource allocations for Signalling Radio Bearer in the DRNC. kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_HS_DSCH_INACTIV_INT

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_EDCH_INACTIV_BGR

kpi_info.title: ATT_HSPA_DIREAL_INT

UPDATED: When HS-DSCH/E-DCH or HS-DSCH/DCH user plane setup is triggered immediately upon receiving RANAP: RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_SUCC_HSPA_DIREAL_BGR

kpi_info.title: ALLO_SUCC_HSPA_DIREAL_INT

kpi_info.title: SETUP_REJ_EDCH_AC_BGR
kpi_info.use: "The number of E-DCH setup failures due to admission control for background class connections. UPDATED: When E-DCH cannot be setup due to uplink admission control rejection. This happens when the averaged estimated Rel99 interference exceeds the limit value defined as the maximum of the values of the management parameters PrxTarget, PrxTargetMax and PrxMaxTargetBTS.The counter is updated only for initial E-DCH allocation attempts, not for channel type switches and serving cell changes."

kpi_info.title: ALLO_HS_DSCH_FLOW_PTT
kpi_info.use: The number of successful HS-DSCH allocations for PTT. Also M1002C385 or M1002C389 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED:When RNC has received RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from PTT UE - after successful HS-DSCH MAC-d flow setup for PTT RAB

kpi_info.title: ALLO_SUCCESS_EDCH_PTT
kpi_info.use: The number of successful E-DCH allocations for PTT. Also M1002C531 or M1002C532 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED:When RNC has received RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE / RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE message from PTT UE - after successful E-DCH MAC-d flow setup for PTT RAB

kpi_info.title: MEH_RESTR_R99_UL_DCH
kpi_info.use: The number of Rel99 UL DCH bitrate selections where the bitrate is restricted due to temporary maximum bitrate of Mass Event Handler feature being active. This counter specifically measures the selections of lower bitrate, regardless of whether the allocation was finally successful from the point-of-view of the UE and other network resource. UPDATED:This counter is updated when the cell specific admission control entity of the RNC selects restricted UL DCH bitrate due to high load detected by Mass Event Handler algorithm.

kpi_info.title: MEH_REJECT_EDCH
kpi_info.use:
The number of UL DCH selections instead of E-DCH due to Mass Event Handler temporary user amount restriction. UPDATED:This counter is updated when the cell specific admission control entity of the RNC does not allow E-DCH allocation due to temporary user amount restriction caused by high cell load.
Also existing UL DCH SELECTED counters like M1002C515, M1002C516 are updated together with this new counter.

kpi_info.title: MEH_REJECT_HSDSCH
kpi_info.use:
The number of DL DCH selections instead of HS-DSCH due to Voice Call Priorization During High Traffic Load temporary user amount restriction. UPDATED:This counter is updated when the cell specific admission control entity of the RNC does not allow HS-DSCH allocation due to temporary user amount restriction applied by Voice Call Priorization During High Traffic Load feature.
Also existing DL DCH SELECTED counters like M1002C475, M1002C476 are updated together with this new counter.

kpi_info.title: MEH_ADMIT_CS_VOICE
kpi_info.use:
The number of CS Voice calls admitted to the cell when (Ptx_nc + delta_Ptx_nc) is greater than PtxTarget. This special admission condition of Voice Call Priorization During High Traffic Load functionality triggers temporary restriction of HSDPA user amount.
This counter specifically measures the successful admission control allocations for CS voice, regardless of whether the allocation was finally successful from the point-of-view of the UE and other network resource. UPDATED:This counter is updated when the cell specific admission control entity of the RNC admits CS Voice call to the cell.

kpi_info.title: MEH_REJECT_2MS_EDCH_TTI
kpi_info.use: The number of times when E-DCH 2 ms TTI allocation is prevented due to high cell load detected by Mass Event Handler functionality. UPDATED:This counter is updated when the cell specific admission control entity of the RNC decides to select 10 ms E-DCH TTI instead of 2 ms TTI due to high cell load.
